This paper deals with unsupervised learning problems, specifically dictionary learning and tensor decomposition. The use of the Sum of Squares semidefinite programming hierarchy is a key aspect of the algorithm, indicating a focus on optimization and mathematical programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) due to the algorithmic nature of the paper. The use of semidefinite programming also suggests a connection to numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on unsupervised learning and the use of the Sum of Squares method for analyzing the algorithm suggest a connection to control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
